description.narrative: The results of the end-line study in Kupang district demonstrates improvements in learning process, teacher-child interactions, and overall engagement with ECE Curriculum and learning resources compared to the baseline study's results. Kupang district government has committed to continue the program with its own resources. At national level, UNICEF supports the Ministry of Education and Culture (MoEC) in preparing HI-ECD replication to 50 selected districts based on experiences of HI-ECD implementation in Bogor and Kupang districts. UNICEF also work closely with the Central Bureau of Statistics in developing an SDG monitoring instrument for ECD by adopting the new ECDI module. | Status:On-track | As-of Date:16/07/2020
